                  <handDesc><!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Hand a: very fine and careful. Hand b: fine</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        <date>Second half of the 18th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donor; incipits of the texts (two initial lines in Text I, III and V; the word ʾo-za-...and the following verbal form in Text I; the word salām in Texts II, III and IV; part of Additio 1; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
&#xD;
On the incipit page of Texts II four lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).&#xD;
On the incipit page of Texts IV two lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
